> He has been charged.<p>&quot;Sweden has yet to formally charge Assange with any offense.&quot; 
- The Guardian<p>&quot;Sweden has yet to formally indict Assange.&quot;
 - New York Times<p>&quot;Mr Assange has not been formally charged with any offense.&quot;
 - BBC<p>&quot;Sweden does not have a time limit on how long the pre-trial stage will last or how long a person can be held in pre-trial detention.... only when an indictment is brought does the suspect acquire the formal rights of the accused.&quot;
